oc:kn_0516562b a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When deciding whether to use the minimal vs. full plugin scaffold" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Use the minimal plugin pattern for quick prototypes, single-purpose utilities, learning plugin development, or internal team tools with one specific function." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Over-engineering a simple utility adds maintenance burden without proportional value." .

oc:kn_052e473a a oc:Idempotency,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When evaluating plugin safety and reusability" ;
    oc:directiveContent "The minimal plugin scaffold has no side effects — it is a static template with no scripts, hooks, or external resource dependencies." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Zero-dependency plugins are inherently safe to install and test without risk to the environment." .

oc:kn_44995d2b a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When scaffolding the simplest possible plugin" ;
    oc:directiveContent "A minimal plugin requires only a .claude-plugin/plugin.json with a 'name' field and a commands/ directory with at least one .md file." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Establishes the absolute minimum contract for a functioning plugin — no scripts, hooks, or external resources needed." .

oc:kn_8296893d a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When evolving a minimal plugin into a full-featured one" ;
    oc:directiveContent "To extend a minimal plugin, progressively add: more .md command files, plugin.json metadata (version, description, author), agents/ directory, and hooks/hooks.json." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Incremental growth avoids big-bang rewrites and lets the plugin mature alongside its use cases." .

oc:kn_bcbcd7b8 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Standard ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When creating plugin commands" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Commands are auto-discovered from .md files in the commands/ directory. Each command file must have YAML frontmatter with 'name' and 'description' fields." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Convention-over-configuration discovery means no registration is needed — Claude Code finds commands automatically." .

